{"_id": "ow_bg001", "name": "Regiment: Cadian Shock Troops", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Athletics, Common Lore (Imperial Guard, War), Operate (Surface), Scholastic Lore (Tactica Imperialis), Survival\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP, Thrown), Combat Formation\n\nStarting Equipment: Lasgun, flak armour, 4 charge packs, 2 frag grenades, 2 krak grenades, combat knife\n\nRegimental Bonus: Superior Tactical Training: +5 to all Intelligence-based tests when following tactical orders. Squad Formation drill bonus applies.\n\nAptitudes: Fieldcraft or Leadership\n\nHomeworld: Cadia \u2014 Fortress World\n\nHistory: Cadian Shock Troops are the gold standard of the Imperial Guard. Drilled from birth, every Cadian is a soldier. Renowned for discipline and tactical flexibility.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Fieldcraft or Leadership | Superior Tactical Training: +5 to all Intelligence-based tests when following tactical orders. Squad Formation drill bonus applies."}}
{"_id": "ow_bg002", "name": "Regiment: Catachan Jungle Fighters", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Athletics, Awareness, Common Lore (Imperial Guard), Survival, Stealth\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP, Primitive), Ambush\n\nStarting Equipment: Shotgun or lasgun, flak armour, knife (Catachan pattern), 2 doses of stimm, grapnel, cameleoline cloak\n\nRegimental Bonus: Child of the Jungle: +10 Survival in any wilderness environment. Ignore difficult terrain in natural settings.\n\nAptitudes: Fieldcraft or Offence\n\nHomeworld: Catachan \u2014 Death World\n\nHistory: Born on one of the deadliest worlds in the Imperium, Catachans are hardened killers who excel at jungle warfare and ambush tactics.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Fieldcraft or Offence | Child of the Jungle: +10 Survival in any wilderness environment. Ignore difficult terrain in natural settings."}}
{"_id": "ow_bg003", "name": "Regiment: Mordian Iron Guard", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Command, Common Lore (Imperial Guard), Intimidate, Linguistics (High Gothic), Scrutiny\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP), Drill\n\nStarting Equipment: Lasgun, dress uniform with flak inserts, 4 charge packs, lho sticks, chrono\n\nRegimental Bonus: Parade Ground Discipline: when unit passes a Command test, all squad members gain +10 to next action. -5 to Stealth tests.\n\nAptitudes: Leadership or Defence\n\nHomeworld: Mordian \u2014 Hive World\n\nHistory: The Mordian Iron Guard are famous for their immaculate dress uniforms and iron discipline. They fight in perfect formation, breaking enemies through sheer firepower.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Leadership or Defence | Parade Ground Discipline: when unit passes a Command test, all squad members gain +10 to next action. -5 to Stealth tests."}}
{"_id": "ow_bg004", "name": "Regiment: Valhallan Ice Warriors", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Athletics, Common Lore (Imperial Guard), Medicae, Survival, Toughness\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP), Die Hard\n\nStarting Equipment: Lasgun, greatcoat (counts as flak armour), 4 charge packs, winter gear kit, flask of Valhallian spirits\n\nRegimental Bonus: Unbreakable: may re-roll failed Toughness tests to resist the effects of fatigue and extreme cold. +5 Toughness in cold environments.\n\nAptitudes: Toughness or Defence\n\nHomeworld: Valhalla \u2014 Ice World\n\nHistory: Forged in the eternal winters of Valhalla, the Ice Warriors are tough, determined soldiers who never give up ground. Famous for holding the line no matter the cost.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Toughness or Defence | Unbreakable: may re-roll failed Toughness tests to resist the effects of fatigue and extreme cold. +5 Toughness in cold environments."}}
{"_id": "ow_bg005", "name": "Regiment: Tallarn Desert Raiders", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Acrobatics, Common Lore (Imperial Guard), Operate (Surface), Stealth, Survival\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP, Bolt), Ambush, Catfall\n\nStarting Equipment: Autopistol, desert robes (counts as flak armour), 3 clips, 2 smoke grenades, respirator, water canteen\n\nRegimental Bonus: Desert Warfare: +20 Stealth in desert environments. Ignore difficult terrain in desert/arid settings. -10 in dense vegetation.\n\nAptitudes: Fieldcraft or Agility\n\nHomeworld: Tallarn \u2014 Desert World\n\nHistory: Survivors of a devastating virus bomb attack, the Tallarn fight a mobile guerrilla war. Masters of ambush, raid, and rapid withdrawal.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Fieldcraft or Agility | Desert Warfare: +20 Stealth in desert environments. Ignore difficult terrain in desert/arid settings. -10 in dense vegetation."}}
{"_id": "ow_bg006", "name": "Regiment: Steel Legion (Armageddon)", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Common Lore (Imperial Guard, War), Operate (Surface), Scholastic Lore (Tactica Imperialis), Tech-Use\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP), Technical Knock\n\nStarting Equipment: Lasgun, flak armour, rebreather, 4 charge packs, grapnel line\n\nRegimental Bonus: Urban Combat Training: +10 to all tests in urban environments. When riding vehicles, may shoot as if stationary.\n\nAptitudes: Fieldcraft or Tech\n\nHomeworld: Armageddon \u2014 Hive World\n\nHistory: Veterans of the Armageddon Wars, the Steel Legion specialize in combined arms warfare and urban combat, working closely with Leman Russ tank squadrons.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Fieldcraft or Tech | Urban Combat Training: +10 to all tests in urban environments. When riding vehicles, may shoot as if stationary."}}
{"_id": "ow_bg007", "name": "Regiment: Elysian Drop Troops", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Acrobatics, Athletics, Common Lore (Imperial Guard), Operate (Aeronautica), Stealth\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP), Catfall, Rapid Reload\n\nStarting Equipment: Hellgun or lasgun, carapace armour, grav-chute, 3 charge packs, 2 krak grenades, micro-bead\n\nRegimental Bonus: Aerial Insertion: may deploy from aircraft without test in safe conditions. +20 Acrobatics when using grav-chute. No penalties from drops up to 50m.\n\nAptitudes: Agility or Fieldcraft\n\nHomeworld: Elysia \u2014 Paradise World\n\nHistory: Elite drop troops who insert by grav-chute behind enemy lines. Heavily armed and trained to fight outnumbered, they strike fast and hard.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Agility or Fieldcraft | Aerial Insertion: may deploy from aircraft without test in safe conditions. +20 Acrobatics when using grav-chute. No penalties from drops up to 50m."}}
{"_id": "ow_bg008", "name": "Regiment: Death Korps of Krieg", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Starting Skills: Athletics, Common Lore (Imperial Guard, War), Medicae, Scholastic Lore (Tactica Imperialis), Toughness\n\nStarting Talents: Weapon Training (Las, SP, Thrown), Resistance (Fear, Poisons)\n\nStarting Equipment: Lasgun, Krieg uniform with flak armour, 4 charge packs, gas mask, entrenching tool, 2 frag grenades\n\nRegimental Bonus: Grim Resolve: immune to Pinning caused by ranged fire when in or behind prepared defensive positions. Morale never drops below 1 from ranged attacks alone.\n\nAptitudes: Toughness or Willpower\n\nHomeworld: Krieg \u2014 Devastated World\n\nHistory: The Death Korps of Krieg are renowned for their fanatical devotion to the Emperor and utter disregard for their own lives. Specialists in siege warfare and trench combat.", "benefit": "Aptitudes: Toughness or Willpower | Grim Resolve: immune to Pinning caused by ranged fire when in or behind prepared defensive positions. Morale never drops below 1 from ranged attacks alone."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro001", "name": "Specialisation: Guardsman", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Agility, Ballistic Skill, Fieldcraft, Offence, Perception\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Quick Draw or Rapid Reload\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Crack Shot: spend Fate to add DoS on ranged attack as bonus damage. The backbone of any regiment.", "benefit": "Crack Shot: spend Fate to add DoS on ranged attack as bonus damage. The backbone of any regiment."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro002", "name": "Specialisation: Weapon Specialist", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Ballistic Skill, Offence, Strength, Toughness, Weapon Skill\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Hip Shooting or Bulging Biceps\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Weight of Fire: when firing Full Auto, add 1 additional hit per 2 DoS instead of per DoS.", "benefit": "Weight of Fire: when firing Full Auto, add 1 additional hit per 2 DoS instead of per DoS."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro003", "name": "Specialisation: Sergeant", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Fellowship, Leadership, Offence, Toughness, Willpower\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Air of Authority or Into the Jaws of Hell\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Squad Leader: once per round as a Free Action, grant one ally within 10m a +10 to their next test.", "benefit": "Squad Leader: once per round as a Free Action, grant one ally within 10m a +10 to their next test."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro004", "name": "Specialisation: Commissar", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Fellowship, Leadership, Offence, Willpower, Social\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Into the Jaws of Hell or Hatred (Enemies of the Imperium)\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Summary Execution: may execute a routing ally to immediately rally all other allies within 30m. They gain +10 to all tests until end of round.", "benefit": "Summary Execution: may execute a routing ally to immediately rally all other allies within 30m. They gain +10 to all tests until end of round."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro005", "name": "Specialisation: Operator", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Agility, Fieldcraft, Intelligence, Offence, Tech\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Technical Knock or Weapon Training (Vehicle)\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Never Lost: never suffer penalties for unfamiliar vehicles. +20 Operate when pushing a vehicle beyond its limits.", "benefit": "Never Lost: never suffer penalties for unfamiliar vehicles. +20 Operate when pushing a vehicle beyond its limits."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro006", "name": "Specialisation: Heavy Gunner", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Ballistic Skill, Offence, Strength, Toughness\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Bulging Biceps or Hip Shooting\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Suppressing Fire: when using Full Auto, enemy units in the area of fire must test Pinning even if not hit.", "benefit": "Suppressing Fire: when using Full Auto, enemy units in the area of fire must test Pinning even if not hit."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro007", "name": "Specialisation: Medic", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Fieldcraft, Intelligence, Knowledge, Toughness\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Resistance (Poisons) or Superior Chirurgeon\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Field Medic: may attempt First Aid as a Half Action instead of Full Action. +10 Medicae tests during combat.", "benefit": "Field Medic: may attempt First Aid as a Half Action instead of Full Action. +10 Medicae tests during combat."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro008", "name": "Specialisation: Ogryn", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Strength, Toughness, Offence\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Unnatural Strength, Bulging Biceps\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Abhuman: counts as Size (Hulking). +20 Strength, -20 Intelligence minimum. Cannot use most equipment. Feared by enemies.", "benefit": "Abhuman: counts as Size (Hulking). +20 Strength, -20 Intelligence minimum. Cannot use most equipment. Feared by enemies."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro009", "name": "Specialisation: Ratling", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Agility, Ballistic Skill, Fieldcraft, Stealth\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Catfall or Marksman\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Small Target: -20 to hit a Ratling. +20 Stealth. Crack shot with a sniper rifle, despite appearing to do nothing useful otherwise.", "benefit": "Small Target: -20 to hit a Ratling. +20 Stealth. Crack shot with a sniper rifle, despite appearing to do nothing useful otherwise."}}
{"_id": "ow_ro010", "name": "Specialisation: Psyker (Sanctioned)", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Specialisation Aptitudes: Intelligence, Knowledge, Psyker, Willpower\n\nSpecialisation Talent: Psyniscience or Resistance (Psychic Powers)\n\nSpecialisation Bonus: Battlefield Psyker: starts with Psy Rating 1 and access to one psychic discipline. May purchase Psy Rating advances with XP.", "benefit": "Battlefield Psyker: starts with Psy Rating 1 and access to one psychic discipline. May purchase Psy Rating advances with XP."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw001", "name": "World: Fortress World", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Toughness +X, Willpower +X | Agility -X | Fate 2 | Blessing 6+\n\nWorld Bonus: Death Before Dishonour: may re-roll failed Fear tests caused by the enemy. +10 Willpower when defending fixed positions.", "benefit": "Death Before Dishonour: may re-roll failed Fear tests caused by the enemy. +10 Willpower when defending fixed positions."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw002", "name": "World: Hive World", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Agility +X, Perception +X | Willpower -X | Fate 2 | Blessing 5+\n\nWorld Bonus: Bred in the Underhive: +20 Stealth in urban environments. +10 Navigate (Surface) in close spaces.", "benefit": "Bred in the Underhive: +20 Stealth in urban environments. +10 Navigate (Surface) in close spaces."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw003", "name": "World: Death World", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Agility +X, Toughness +X | Fellowship -X | Fate 2 | Blessing 4+\n\nWorld Bonus: Born Survivor: +10 Survival tests. Immune to natural poisons and diseases encountered on Death Worlds.", "benefit": "Born Survivor: +10 Survival tests. Immune to natural poisons and diseases encountered on Death Worlds."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw004", "name": "World: Feral World", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Strength +X, Toughness +X | Intelligence -X | Fate 2 | Blessing 3+\n\nWorld Bonus: Primitive Fighter: Low-Tech weapons lose Primitive quality, gain Proven (3). +10 Athletics.", "benefit": "Primitive Fighter: Low-Tech weapons lose Primitive quality, gain Proven (3). +10 Athletics."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw005", "name": "World: Civilised World", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Fellowship +X, Intelligence +X | Toughness -X | Fate 3 | Blessing 7+\n\nWorld Bonus: Educated: start with one additional Common Lore or Scholastic Lore skill at Known (free).", "benefit": "Educated: start with one additional Common Lore or Scholastic Lore skill at Known (free)."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw006", "name": "World: Agri-World", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Strength +X, Fellowship +X | Agility -X | Fate 2 | Blessing 6+\n\nWorld Bonus: Hardy Stock: +10 Toughness tests to resist hunger, thirst, and physical hardship.", "benefit": "Hardy Stock: +10 Toughness tests to resist hunger, thirst, and physical hardship."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw007", "name": "World: Forge World", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Intelligence +X, Toughness +X | Fellowship -X | Fate 3 | Blessing 8+\n\nWorld Bonus: Machine Touched: +10 Tech-Use. Starts with Mechanicus Implants trait.", "benefit": "Machine Touched: +10 Tech-Use. Starts with Mechanicus Implants trait."}}
{"_id": "ow_hw008", "name": "World: Voidborn", "type": "trait", "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg", "system": {"description": "Characteristics: Intelligence +X, Willpower +X | Strength -X | Fate 3 | Blessing 5+\n\nWorld Bonus: Void Acclimatised: +30 tests in zero-gravity. Starts with Strong Minded talent.", "benefit": "Void Acclimatised: +30 tests in zero-gravity. Starts with Strong Minded talent."}}
